a.n: Led Zeppelin - The Song Remains the Same

p.d: The Song Remains the Same is a 1976 concert film featuring the English rock band Led Zeppelin. The filming took place during the summer of 1973, during three nights of concerts at Madison Square Garden in New York City. The album was originally released in October 1976, before being remastered and reissued in 2007 and again in September 2018.
